.TH enckode 1 "@PROJECT_YEAR@" "@PROJECT_VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
enckode \- hacker cipher encrypt/decrypt helper
.br
deckode \- enckode decryption alias
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B enckode
.RI [ OPTION ]... [ args ]...
.br
.B deckode
.RI [ OPTION ]... [ args ]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Encrypt/decrypt using a shared dictionary-based reversible transform.
.PP
If no args are provided, reads one message from standard input.
.PP
.B deckode
is installed as a symlink to
.BR enckode .
When invoked as
.B deckode
the default mode is decryption (equivalent to passing
.BR --decrypt ).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-D ", " \-\-dict\ FILE
Dictionary source. If FILE ends with
.B .map
it is treated as a precompiled mmap image. Otherwise it's treated as a text
dictionary (one word per line). Empty lines and lines starting with
.B #
are ignored.
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-encrypt
Encryption mode (default).
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-decrypt
Decryption mode.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-number
Number mode: operate on base-N div tokens as decimal numbers.
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-auto
Auto detect each encryption arg as number or string (numbers are treated as number by default unless --string).
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-string
Always treat encryption args as strings (overrides --auto).
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-stdout
Output to standard output (default).
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable more logging.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Reduce logging.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display this help and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Output version and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred (invalid options, unreadable dict file, or transform failure).
.SH AUTHOR
Written by @PROJECT_AUTHOR@ <@PROJECT_EMAIL@>.
